What is the meaning of moody Monday?

"Moody Monday" generally refers to feeling grumpy, irritable, or unhappy at the start of the workweek, possibly due to the end of the weekend and the return to regular responsibilities. It signifies a negative mood or attitude on Mondays.

Is the word moody a noun?

No, "moody" is an adjective, used to describe a person's tendency to exhibit frequent changes in mood.
